Model:Class.name: ConsoleControl
Model:Class.annotation: The ConsoleControl class provides a simple text based interface for the game of turn based pacman.

Model:Attribute.name: MSG_BAD_INPUT
Model:Attribute.annotation: Bad input message.

Model:Attribute.name: MSG_THANK_YOU
Model:Attribute.annotation: Thank you for playing message.

Model:Attribute.name: MSG_PLAY_AGAIN
Model:Attribute.annotation: Play again message.

Model:Attribute.name: YES_KEY
Model:Attribute.annotation: the keys used to play the game

Model:Attribute.name: bi
Model:Attribute.annotation: Buffered input for reading in characters

Model:Attribute.name: continueGame
Model:Attribute.annotation: Game State

Model:Operation.name: ConsoleControl
Model:Operation.annotation: Creates a Console Controller for use in the tb-pacman game

Model:Operation.name: execute
Model:Operation.annotation: Simple execution method. If w,a,s or d are pressed pacman will move in it's respective direction. If q is pressed the game will end. @return True if the game is to continue to execute. False if game is complete.

Model:Operation.name: gameOver
Model:Operation.annotation: Should a gameOver Event be broadcast, the controller will end the game.

Model:Operation.name: levelComplete
Model:Operation.annotation: Prompts the player to start a new game when they beat the level. In the full game, this should probably load the next level.

Model:EnumerationType.name: ControlCommand
Model:EnumerationType.annotation: Enum class for all the possible control commands the controller is configured to handle. Any class using this controller should send action events with one of these control codes as a ActionCommand to invoke the desired response from the controller.

Model:Class.name: PacShell
Model:Class.annotation: PacShell class serves to initialise a test level, and all resources needed to run an instance of turn-based pacman

Model:Class.name: Controller
Model:Class.annotation: The Control class provides control of the model.

Model:Attribute.name: QUIT_KEY
Model:Attribute.annotation: The following are the keys used to play the game

Model:Attribute.name: wait
Model:Attribute.annotation: Time used for reducing the number of keyTyped events

Model:Attribute.name: useKey
Model:Attribute.annotation: Execute move flag

Model:Attribute.name: reset
Model:Attribute.annotation: reset key press flag

Model:Attribute.name: levelPass
Model:Attribute.annotation: level complete flag

Model:Operation.name: Controller
Model:Operation.annotation: Creates a Console Controller for use in the tb-pacman game

Model:Operation.name: handleEvent
Model:Operation.annotation: This method should handle the majority of interaction with the actual game model.

Model:Operation.name: keyTyped
Model:Operation.annotation: Simple execution method that will only update the model if the useKey flag is true. If so it will start the timer (time until next move can occur) and set the flag to false. If w,a,s or d are pressed pacman will move in it's respective direction. If q is pressed the game will end. (Fixed)

Model:Operation.name: actionPerformed
Model:Operation.annotation: Resends the ActionEvent info to PerformAction()

Model:Operation.name: levelComplete
Model:Operation.annotation: Should the level be completed, the control should load a new level the next time the player presses "space".

Model:EnumerationType.name: GameEntity
Model:EnumerationType.annotation: The GameEntity enum is used to identify all valid types of game entities which can be placed as spawn points in a game level.

Model:Class.name: GameListenerAdapter
Model:Class.annotation: GameListenerAdapter defines the functions that a class may want implement while listening to the GameModel class. Derived from the GameListener Interface by Alex Craig

Model:Operation.name: playerMove
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called whenever the player successfully makes a move.

Model:Operation.name: playerDeath
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called whenever the player dies.

Model:Operation.name: levelReset
Model:Operation.annotation: This function is called whenever the game level is reset for any reason.

Model:Operation.name: gameOver
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called if the player loses all their lives.

Model:Operation.name: levelComplete
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called when every dot on the grid has been collected.

Model:Operation.name: newGame
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called when ever a new Game has been created

Model:EnumerationType.name: Direction
Model:EnumerationType.annotation: The Direction enumeration is used to identify the cardinal directions.

Model:Class.name: Maze
Model:Class.annotation: The Maze class stores a grid of game tiles. It includes functionality to add and remove tiles from the grid, and automatically adds and removes the corresponding exits to these tiles. Walls within the maze are simply modelled by the absence of exits. This allows for one sided walls, portals, wrap around and all sorts of other awesomeness. Maze class also supports iteration over the contained tiles.

Model:Reference.name: tile
Model:Reference.annotation: stores the grid of maze tiles, indexed by their x,y coordinates

Model:Attribute.name: maxX
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores the maximum rows in the maze (from 0 to 1 less than this value)

Model:Attribute.name: maxY
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores the maximum columns in the maze (from 0 to 1 less than this value)

Model:Attribute.name: passDots
Model:Attribute.annotation: the required dots remaining to pass the maze

Model:Operation.name: Maze
Model:Operation.annotation: Generates a new maze with the specified maximum size

Model:Operation.name: addTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Adds a new tile to the maze at the specified x, y position, given that the position is currently empty. Automatically adds exits to adjacent tiles. @return true if the add was successful, false if the position is already filled or invalid position passed

Model:Operation.name: removeTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Removes the tile at the specified x, y coordinates @return true if the tile was successfully removed, false if no tile existed at the given position

Model:Operation.name: getTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns the tile at the specified x, y coordinates @return null if no tile was found at the specified location or if the index was invalid

Model:Operation.name: getNeighbour
Model:Operation.annotation: Gets the tile neighbouring a given tile in the maze. @return null if no neighbour exists, or the neighbour tile

Model:Operation.name: clearMaze
Model:Operation.annotation: Clears the maze of all tiles.

Model:Operation.name: dotsRemaining
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the number of unvisited tiles (dots) remaining in the maze

Model:Operation.name: isComplete
Model:Operation.annotation: @return true if the maze has the less than or equal to the remaining number of dots required to clear the maze, false if the maze cleared

Model:Operation.name: addExit
Model:Operation.annotation: Adds an exit to the specified tile in the specified direction. Also can add a return exit from the neighbouring tile to the current tile. Requires that another tile already exists in the specified direction. @return false if the add failed for any reason (ie. tile does not exist, neighbour does not exist, exits already exist)

Model:Operation.name: removeExit
Model:Operation.annotation: Removes an exit from the specified tile. Also can remove the return exit from the neighbouring tile to the current tile. Requires that the tile exist, and that it has an exit in the given direction. @return false if the remove failed for any reason (ie. tile does not exist, exits do not exist)

Model:Operation.name: getMaxX
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the maximum x coordinate in this maze (from 0 to maxX - 1)

Model:Operation.name: getMaxY
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the maximum y coordinate in this maze (from 0 to maxY - 1)

Model:Operation.name: setPassDots
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the number of dots remaining needed to pass the maze

Model:Operation.name: getPassDots
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the number of dots remaining needed to pass the maze

Model:Class.name: Tile
Model:Class.annotation: Tile class represents one movement square within the game world. Each tile stores a list of neighbouring tiles, as well as a flag which stores whether the tile has been visited by the player or not.

Model:Attribute.name: visited
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores whether the tile has been visited by the player

Model:Attribute.name: xCoord
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores the x coordinate of the tile in relation to the maze grid

Model:Attribute.name: yCoord
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores the y coordinate of the tile in relation to the maze grid

Model:Attribute.name: exits
Model:Attribute.annotation: the list of possible exits from the tile (only cardinal direction allowed)

Model:Operation.name: Tile
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructs a new tile at the given coordinates. The new tile has no neighbours, and has not been visited.

Model:Operation.name: hasDot
Model:Operation.annotation: @return true if the tile has not been visited, false if it has

Model:Operation.name: getXCoord
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the x coordinate of the tile in relation to the maze grid

Model:Operation.name: getYCoord
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the y coordinate of the tile in relation to the maze grid

Model:Operation.name: clearDot
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the visited status of the tile to true (ie. no dot should be drawn).

Model:Operation.name: resetDot
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the visited status of the tile to false (ie. a dot should be drawn)

Model:Operation.name: setExit
Model:Operation.annotation: Adds an exit to the tile. An exit may not be added to a direction with an existing exit unless the original exit is removed first. @return returns true if the add was successful, false if a duplicate key was encountered

Model:Operation.name: removeExit
Model:Operation.annotation: Removes a given exit from the tile. @return false if the exit did not exist, true otherwise

Model:Operation.name: getExit
Model:Operation.annotation: Gets the exit in the specified direction. @return returns the tile in the given direction, or null if no exit exists

Model:Operation.name: shortName
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns of a string of the tile's x and y coordinates. Mostly for debug purposes. @return a string in the format of "Tile X:n Y:n"

Model:Operation.name: toString
Model:Operation.annotation: @return a long string description of the tile and it's exits

Model:Class.name: Player
Model:Class.annotation: A Player type Character. This Character is human controlled.

Model:Attribute.name: DEATH_POINTS
Model:Attribute.annotation: The number of points lost for a death

Model:Attribute.name: DOT_POINTS
Model:Attribute.annotation: The number of points rewarded for eating a dot

Model:Attribute.name: lives
Model:Attribute.annotation: The number of lives that a Player has. Zero Lives means game over.

Model:Attribute.name: score
Model:Attribute.annotation: The players current score.

Model:Operation.name: Player
Model:Operation.annotation: Creates a new PLayer object and places it in the Maze.

Model:Operation.name: loseLife
Model:Operation.annotation: Decrement's the number of lives this Player has and removes DEATH_POINTS number of points from the players score. @return True if the Player has lost his last life.

Model:Operation.name: getLives
Model:Operation.annotation: Retrieves the number of lives this Player has. @return number of lives.

Model:Operation.name: setLives
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the players live to the specified value, given that it is positive

Model:Operation.name: isDead
Model:Operation.annotation: Checks the number of lives this Player has and determines if its zero. @return True if there are zero lives left.

Model:Operation.name: getScore
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns the players current score. @return The players current score.

Model:Operation.name: setTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets a new Tile as the Character's current position, provided the tile is not null. If the tile is null, nothing occurs and false is returned. @return True if successful.

Model:Class.name: SpawnPoint
Model:Class.annotation: SpawnPoint class represents a spawn point which can be included in a GameLevel object. This class simply stores a tile and a identifier to indicate what kind of game entity should be spawned at tile.

Model:Reference.name: tile
Model:Reference.annotation: stores the tile which this spawn point should be placed at

Model:Attribute.name: gameEnt
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores what kind of game entity should be spawned at this point

Model:Operation.name: SpawnPoint
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructor for SpawnPoint objects

Model:Operation.name: getSpawnTile
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the tile this spawn point refers to, or null if no tile is set

Model:Operation.name: getSpawnType
Model:Operation.annotation: @return a GameEntity defining what type of game entity should spawn at this point, or null if no spawn type is set

Model:Class.name: GameModel
Model:Class.annotation: GameModel is the main class of the game's model. It can see and control all aspects of the game, and can notify the view and controller of changes to the game state through its inheritance of the Observable class. Its functions include loading gameLevels from file, loading them up, controlling the game Characters, executing move functions and beginning and ending the game.

Model:Attribute.name: PLAYERS_STARTING_LIVES
Model:Attribute.annotation: The number of lives a player is to start the game with.

Model:Reference.name: player
Model:Reference.annotation: The game's main human controlled Character.

Model:Attribute.name: ghosts
Model:Attribute.annotation: A List of Ghost Characters.

Model:Reference.name: gamelevel
Model:Reference.annotation: The current GameLevel that is loaded.

Model:Attribute.name: levels
Model:Attribute.annotation: A List of all Level files the game can access and load.

Model:Attribute.name: listeners
Model:Attribute.annotation: A list of all listeners to this game object

Model:Attribute.name: inProgress
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores whether pacman can make a move at this point

Model:Operation.name: GameModel
Model:Operation.annotation: Loads a game using the given GameLevel. This function is mostly for testing purposes, as the full game will use a list of file names to generate levels. @param levelListFilename

Model:Operation.name: loadLevel
Model:Operation.annotation: Loads a level from file and loads all of its attributes.

Model:Operation.name: makeMove
Model:Operation.annotation: Makes the Player move in the specified Direction, then immediately calls updateGhosts() to move the ghosts. @return True if the move was executed. False if the move couldn't execute (ie. there is a wall in that direction).

Model:Operation.name: updateGhosts
Model:Operation.annotation: After a Player has moved, this method iterates through the ghosts List and calls upon their update methods (ie. determine direction of travel, then move self.)

Model:Operation.name: stateCheck
Model:Operation.annotation: Checks the various events (player death, level complete) that can happen during the game, and sends events accordingly.

Model:Operation.name: getPlayer
Model:Operation.annotation: @return The Player Character

Model:Operation.name: getGhost
Model:Operation.annotation: @return The Ghost at the specified index.

Model:Operation.name: getNumGhosts
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the number of ghosts currently in the maze.

Model:Operation.name: resetGame
Model:Operation.annotation: Resets the entire game (reloads the level, and resets the player's lives to 3).

Model:Operation.name: resetLevel
Model:Operation.annotation: Has the level reset to its initial load state (ie. Characters return start positions, all Tiles have dots put back in them, lives reset.)

Model:Operation.name: addGameListener
Model:Operation.annotation: Adds a game listener to the list of objects listening on this GameModel.

Model:Operation.name: removeGameListener
Model:Operation.annotation: Removes a game listener to the list of objects listening on this GameModel.

Model:Operation.name: getMaze
Model:Operation.annotation: @return The currently loaded Maze.

Model:Class.name: GameEvent
Model:Class.annotation: GameEvent represents an event generated by a GameModel object. This class stores the source GameModel, and can be used to pass additional details on the event.

Model:Operation.name: GameEvent
Model:Operation.annotation: Generates a new GameEvent @param eventType

Model:Operation.name: getSource
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns the source GameModel of the event. @return the source of the event

Model:Class.name: MazeIterator
Model:Class.annotation: MazeIterator allows client classes to iterate through the tiles stored in a maze without any knowledge of the underlying data structure. Tiles are returned in a left to right, top to bottom manner, given that (0,0) is in the top left of the coordinate system, and x and y increase across and down.

Model:Reference.name: tile
Model:Reference.annotation: the reference to the array of tiles

Model:Attribute.name: maxX
Model:Attribute.annotation: the x coordinate boundary for the array

Model:Attribute.name: maxY
Model:Attribute.annotation: the y coordinate boundary for the array

Model:Attribute.name: xPointer
Model:Attribute.annotation: the x coordinate next to be retrieved

Model:Attribute.name: yPointer
Model:Attribute.annotation: the y coordinate next to be retrieved

Model:Operation.name: MazeIterator
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructs a new MazeIterator

Model:Class.name: Ghost
Model:Class.annotation: A Ghost character. Its main purpose in Turn-Based Pacman is to select and chase another Character type around the Maze.

Model:Attribute.name: HORIZONTAL
Model:Attribute.annotation: the movePreference identifier to make the ghost favour horizontal movement

Model:Attribute.name: VERTICAL
Model:Attribute.annotation: the movePreference identifier to make the ghost favour vertical movement

Model:Attribute.name: RANDOM
Model:Attribute.annotation: the movePreference identifier to make the ghost select randomly from valid moves

Model:Attribute.name: MAX_MOVE_ATTEMPTS
Model:Attribute.annotation: the maximum number of times a ghost will try to find a valid move before failing

Model:Reference.name: character
Model:Reference.annotation: The Character that the ghost is meant to chase.

Model:Attribute.name: movePreference
Model:Attribute.annotation: determines what direction the ghost will attempt to move when 2 moves are equally close to the target

Model:Operation.name: Ghost
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructor for objects of type Ghost. Creates a new Ghost type character. movePreference defaults to favour vertical movement.

Model:Operation.name: Ghost
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructor for objects of type Ghost. Creates a new Ghost type character.

Model:Operation.name: getMovePreference
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the identifier for the ghost's movement characteristics

Model:Operation.name: getNextMove
Model:Operation.annotation: Determines the tile that the ghost should move to next. @return the adjacent tile in the direction the ghost should move in, or null if no move should be made

Model:Class.name: GameLevel
Model:Class.annotation: GameLevel contains all the information needed for a complete level for turn based pacman. This includes the game maze itself, as well as the starting tiles for the player and the ghosts

Model:Reference.name: tile
Model:Reference.annotation: Stores the starting location of the player. Note that this is stored separately from other spawn points, as only one can ever exist in a level.

Model:Attribute.name: spawnPoints
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores the spawn points of all game entities

Model:Operation.name: GameLevel
Model:Operation.annotation: Generates a new level with the given maze. This maze should not be replaced once the level object has been created.

Model:Operation.name: isComplete
Model:Operation.annotation: @return true if every tile on the maze has been visited, false if not

Model:Operation.name: getMaze
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns the underlying maze structure. This will most likely be required by the view to draw the game area. @return the underlying maze structure

Model:Operation.name: setPlayerStart
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the player start to the passed tile. No function if null.

Model:Operation.name: clearPlayerStart
Model:Operation.annotation: Clears the player starting point.

Model:Operation.name: addSpawnPoint
Model:Operation.annotation: Adds a new spawn point to the level.

Model:Operation.name: clearSpawnPoint
Model:Operation.annotation: Removes the specified spawn point from the level. @return false if an invalid index was passed, true if the remove was successful

Model:Operation.name: getNumSpawnPoints
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the number of spawn points present in the level.

Model:Operation.name: getPlayerStart
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the starting tile of the player, or null if none has been defined

Model:Operation.name: getSpawnPoint
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns the specified ghost starting point. @return null if invalid index is passed, or a ghost starting tile otherwise

Model:Class.name: Character
Model:Class.annotation: Character models a game entity, be it human or AI controlled, that resides in and can move around a Maze. This class has methods to move around the maze and to access the maze's tiles. Inheriting classes can implement specific behaviour or characteristics.

Model:Reference.name: tile
Model:Reference.annotation: A reference to the Tile that the Character is occupying.

Model:Attribute.name: lastMove
Model:Attribute.annotation: The direction of the characters last movement

Model:Operation.name: Character
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructor of objects of type Character.

Model:Operation.name: getLastMove
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the direction of the characters last move, or null if the character has not moved since being created

Model:Operation.name: setLastMove
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the character last move to the specified direction. Useful for path finding algorithms that return a tile instead of a direction.

Model:Operation.name: move
Model:Operation.annotation: Moves the Character one Tile in the desired Direction. @return True if the move was a success. False if it failed (ie. there is no exit in the Direction.

Model:Operation.name: getNeighbour
Model:Operation.annotation: Gets the Tile adjacent to this Character's current Tile in the desired Direction. @return The Tile that the exit in that Direction leads to. Returns null if the exit contains a null reference (a wall in the Maze).

Model:Operation.name: setTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets a new Tile as the Character's current position, provided the tile is not null. If the tile is null, nothing occurs and false is returned. @return True if successful.

Model:Operation.name: getTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Gets the tile that the Character currently resides in. @return The current tile.

Model:Class.name: ConsoleView
Model:Class.annotation: The ConsoleView class provides a simple, text based way to visualise the game of turn based pacman. In it's current implementation, this class does not support accurate display of one sided walls and portals. This class is primarily for early game play testing purposes.

Model:Attribute.name: MSG_LEVEL_WON
Model:Attribute.annotation: Message displayed if the level was passed.

Model:Attribute.name: MSG_GAME_OVER
Model:Attribute.annotation: Message displayed if the player lost the game.

Model:Attribute.name: MSG_DEATH
Model:Attribute.annotation: Message displayed if a life was lost.

Model:Attribute.name: GHOST_SYMBOL
Model:Attribute.annotation: the symbols used to construct the map

Model:Operation.name: ConsoleView
Model:Operation.annotation: Default Constructor

Model:Operation.name: ConsoleView
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructs the ConsolveView, and starts it listening to a given GameModel.

Model:Operation.name: drawMaze
Model:Operation.annotation: Draws a graphical representation of a pacman maze to the console. @param maze the maze to draw

Model:Operation.name: playerMove
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called whenever the player successfully makes a move. @param EventObject stores the source and additional details on the event

Model:Operation.name: playerDeath
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called whenever the player dies. @param EventObject stores the source and additional details on the event

Model:Operation.name: gameOver
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called if the player loses all their lives. @param EventObject stores the source and additional details on the event

Model:Operation.name: levelComplete
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called when every dot on the grid has been collected. @param EventObject stores the source and additional details on the event

Model:Class.name: PacFrame
Model:Class.annotation: PacFrame class represents the main frame for the GUI view of tb-pacman. This frame is designed to listen on a single GameModel object.

Model:Attribute.name: UI_HEIGHT
Model:Attribute.annotation: extra height required for the user interface

Model:Attribute.name: UI_WIDTH
Model:Attribute.annotation: extra width required for the user interface

Model:Attribute.name: DEFAULT_FONT_SIZE
Model:Attribute.annotation: default font information

Model:Attribute.name: TEAM_INFO
Model:Attribute.annotation: design Teams information.

Model:Attribute.name: MENU_ABOUT
Model:Attribute.annotation: text for the game menus

Model:Attribute.name: MSG_LOOK_AND_FEEL_FAIL
Model:Attribute.annotation: error message for the event in which the look and feel for the OS fail to load

Model:Attribute.name: GAME_TITLE
Model:Attribute.annotation: the games title

Model:Attribute.name: VERSION_ID
Model:Attribute.annotation: the version number to be displayed on the UI

Model:Reference.name: gamemodel
Model:Reference.annotation: the game model to be watched by this view

Model:Reference.name: paccanvas
Model:Reference.annotation: the canvas which draws the majority of the game information

Model:Attribute.name: infoLabel
Model:Attribute.annotation: the label used to show splash screens and other information

Model:Operation.name: PacFrame
Model:Operation.annotation: Generates a new PacFrame listening on the given GameModel. Each PacFrame can only listen on one GameModel at a time, and will ignore all events from other sources.

Model:Operation.name: createImageIcon
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns an ImageIcon, or null if the path was invalid.

Model:Class.name: PacCanvas
Model:Class.annotation: PacCanvas provides the main game window for a game of tb-pacman. This canvas will handle the display of all non-interactive elements of a game of tb-pacman (i.e. the game maze, score of life displays... etc.). In order to provide a smooth game experience, this canvas is double buffered. The smooth animation of game sprites is a bit of a kludge (using swing timers), but thread interference was an issue I was not able to tackle given the time frame.

Model:Attribute.name: SETTINGS_LOW
Model:Attribute.annotation: these represent the possible graphics presets for the game

Model:Attribute.name: TILE_SPREAD
Model:Attribute.annotation: the width/height of each tile (in pixels)

Model:Attribute.name: FRAME_LENGTH
Model:Attribute.annotation: the length of time in ms that a frame lasts

Model:Attribute.name: MOUTH_TIMER_LENGTH
Model:Attribute.annotation: the length of time in ms that the mouth lasts

Model:Attribute.name: MSG_LEVEL_START
Model:Attribute.annotation: game messages used to display information to the player

Model:Attribute.name: DEFAULT_FONT_SIZE
Model:Attribute.annotation: default font information

Model:Attribute.name: DOT_SIZE
Model:Attribute.annotation: the radius of the tile dots (in pixels)

Model:Attribute.name: EYE_SIZE
Model:Attribute.annotation: the radius of the eyes for the ghosts (in pixels)

Model:Attribute.name: WALL_WIDTH
Model:Attribute.annotation: the width of the outer walls and portals (in pixels)

Model:Attribute.name: WALL_SPACING
Model:Attribute.annotation: how far apart the walls should be for double outlined walls (in pixels)

Model:Attribute.name: PAC_SIZE
Model:Attribute.annotation: the size of pacman (radius) and ghosts (approximate height) (in pixels)

Model:Attribute.name: PORTAL_SPACING
Model:Attribute.annotation: how far from walls portal entrances should lie (in pixels)

Model:Attribute.name: MOVE_TIME
Model:Attribute.annotation: how long a single tile movement should take (in ms)

Model:Attribute.name: PORTAL_COLORS
Model:Attribute.annotation: The list of portal colors to be used. Note: portals will repeat this sequence if the total number of portals on a level exceeds the number of colors in this list.

Model:Attribute.name: VERT_GHOST_COLOR
Model:Attribute.annotation: the colors to be used for the three ghost types

Model:Attribute.name: mazeWalls
Model:Attribute.annotation: the list of all walls for the current level

Model:Attribute.name: mazePortals
Model:Attribute.annotation: the list of all portals for the current level

Model:Attribute.name: bufferStrategy
Model:Attribute.annotation: used for double buffering

Model:Attribute.name: mouthTimer
Model:Attribute.annotation: timer used for drawing pacman's mouth

Model:Attribute.name: mouthFrame
Model:Attribute.annotation: determines whether pacman's mouth is open or closed

Model:Attribute.name: frameTimer
Model:Attribute.annotation: timer used for smooth drawing of game movements

Model:Attribute.name: moveEnd
Model:Attribute.annotation: the system time (in ms) when the current move should end

Model:Attribute.name: lastFrameMs
Model:Attribute.annotation: the system time (in ms) of the last update

Model:Attribute.name: settings
Model:Attribute.annotation: used to store what graphic settings should be used to render the game

Model:Attribute.name: overlay
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores the string that the display should overlay over the game area

Model:Attribute.name: wallOutline
Model:Attribute.annotation: the stroke to be used for wall outlines

Model:Attribute.name: wallInner
Model:Attribute.annotation: the stroke to be used for wall interiors

Model:Attribute.name: exitStroke
Model:Attribute.annotation: the stroke to be used for portal exits

Model:Attribute.name: entranceStroke
Model:Attribute.annotation: the stroke to be used for portal entrances

Model:Operation.name: PacCanvas
Model:Operation.annotation: Makes a new instance of PacCanvas, listening on the specified GameModel. Each PacCanvas can only listen on one GameModel at a time, and will ignore all other events.

Model:Operation.name: addNotify
Model:Operation.annotation: This function is called when the PacCanvas is added to a container and sets up the double buffering.

Model:Operation.name: isMoving
Model:Operation.annotation: @return true if a move is currently being drawn

Model:Operation.name: loadLevel
Model:Operation.annotation: Generates a listing of all graphical elements needed to draw the given maze. The graphical maze layout is only recalculated when this function is called, to avoid performance loss due to recalculation on every frame. This function needs to be called every time a new level is loaded.

Model:Operation.name: update
Model:Operation.annotation: Called by the repaint function. This function should clear the back buffer, and then call paint().

Model:Operation.name: paint
Model:Operation.annotation: Paints the current maze status onto the PacCanvas

Model:Operation.name: drawStatusUI
Model:Operation.annotation: Draws the dots, lives and score indicators onto the passed graphics buffer.

Model:Operation.name: drawMazeWalls
Model:Operation.annotation: Draws the walls for the currently loaded maze onto the passed buffer.

Model:Operation.name: drawPortalEntrances
Model:Operation.annotation: Draws the portal entrances for the currently loaded maze onto the passed buffer.

Model:Operation.name: drawPortalExits
Model:Operation.annotation: Draws the portal exits for the currently loaded maze onto the passed buffer.

Model:Operation.name: drawMazeDots
Model:Operation.annotation: Draws white dots in the center of each tile of the passed maze onto the passed buffer.

Model:Operation.name: drawPacman
Model:Operation.annotation: Draws pacman onto the passed buffer. The sprite is automatically offset for the current tile of the passed character, as well as offset for a player move currently taking place.

Model:Operation.name: drawGhost
Model:Operation.annotation: Draws a ghost onto the passed buffer. The sprite is automatically offset for the current tile of the passed character, as well as offset for a player move currently taking place.

Model:Operation.name: translate
Model:Operation.annotation: Translates the passed Graphics object for character movement based on the movement end time, the last frame time, and the direction of character movement. @param currentTime The current system time in ms. This needs to be a parameter as this function could be called several times in a single frame, and should use the same time for every call in a frame.

Model:Operation.name: loadSettings
Model:Operation.annotation: Loads rendering settings into the passed graphics object based on the current selected graphics present. @see PacCanvas.setSettings()

Model:Operation.name: setSettings
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the rendering settings for the PacCanvas to 1 of 3 presets.
